This paper deals with the security of cryptographic protocols in the presence of tamper-proof hardware tokens, which is a topic closely related to computer security (cs.CR). The paper also discusses the feasibility of cryptographic protocols in different settings, which involves information theory (cs.IT) and complexity theory (cs.CC). Additionally, the paper considers the potential vulnerabilities and attacks that can be launched against the hardware tokens, which is a topic in cybersecurity (cs.CY) and software engineering (cs.SE).
